CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1951, p. 8, reads: "GETS HONORARY POLICE BADGES - Josephine Baker, continental stage star, gets an honorary membership in Hill City and accepts symbolic police badges for Dean Martin and Jerry Lewis, comedians who gave a benefit for Hill City last October. Left to right: Safety Director George E. A. Fairley, Miss Baker, Hill City Director Howard C. McKinney and Leslie Powell, Hill City Youth, who made the presentation."
TitMainTitle: Josephine Baker accepting Hill City membership card from Leslie Powell, with George Fairley holding police badges honoring Dean Martin and Jerry Lewis, and Howard McKinney and Jo Bouillon in background
